1
00:00:42,584 --> 00:00:44,545
Blue, 18.

2
00:00:45,921 --> 00:00:48,090
Set. Hit. Hit.

3
00:00:55,389 --> 00:00:59,935
Zach. Zach. Crossbuck 30.
Crossbuck 30.

4
00:01:00,060 --> 00:01:02,271
Crossbuck 30. Crossbuck 30.

5
00:01:02,396 --> 00:01:04,356
- Ready?
- Ready.

6
00:01:04,481 --> 00:01:06,817
<i>The Eagles will have to go for it</i>
<i>on fourth down</i>

7
00:01:06,900 --> 00:01:09,862
with just 42 seconds left in the game
and no timeouts.

8
00:01:09,987 --> 00:01:13,949
<i>Coach Taylor can get his first winning</i>
<i>season for the Shiloh Christian Academy</i>

9
00:01:14,074 --> 00:01:16,034
<i>if they can pull this play off.</i>

10
00:01:16,159 --> 00:01:19,121
Move it, team! Set, hit!

11
00:01:19,204 --> 00:01:25,169
<i>Zach Avery pitches back to Jacob Hall.</i>
<i>Jeremy Johnson's going down the field.</i>

12
00:01:25,294 --> 00:01:27,379
- <i>Here come the Tigers.</i>
- Throw it, Jacob!

13
00:01:27,504 --> 00:01:31,508
<i>Jacob's gonna try to tuck it and run,</i>
<i>and he's taken down at the 40-yard line,</i>

14
00:01:31,633 --> 00:01:33,302
<i>stopped by Lewis Slaughter.</i>

15
00:01:33,427 --> 00:01:35,637
<i>Jeremy Johnson was wide open.</i>

16
00:01:35,721 --> 00:01:40,517
<i>If he'd had a few seconds more, this</i>
<i>game might have had a different outcome.</i>

17
00:01:40,642 --> 00:01:44,646
As it is, the Tigers will take over now
and will no doubt run out the clock,

18
00:01:44,771 --> 00:01:49,026
<i>ending Coach Grant Taylor's bid for</i>
<i>his first winning season in six years.</i>

19
00:01:49,151 --> 00:01:53,447
<i>Now he'll have to wait until next season</i>
<i>for that all-elusive winning record.</i>

20
00:01:54,573 --> 00:01:57,117
That's if they let him
come back next year.

21
00:04:08,248 --> 00:04:09,541
- Hi.
- Get 'em, Claire.

22
00:04:09,666 --> 00:04:14,296
Hey, Grant. Come on, y'all.
Quit talking. Let's go, let's go. Hurry.

23
00:04:22,846 --> 00:04:24,806
What?

24
00:04:31,355 --> 00:04:34,483
What? You gotta be kidding me.

25
00:04:35,651 --> 00:04:38,362
- This had better be a joke.
- No.

26
00:04:38,487 --> 00:04:42,115
Mandy said he came in this morning,
got his papers.

27
00:04:42,199 --> 00:04:46,328
A player can't just transfer to another
school. He's gotta change his address.

28
00:04:46,411 --> 00:04:48,914
He did. He's moving in with his dad.

29
00:05:00,259 --> 00:05:03,929
I can't believe that. This is
the third time this has happened.

30
00:05:04,054 --> 00:05:06,348
Spend three years pouring into 'em

31
00:05:06,431 --> 00:05:10,143
and when they get to their senior year,
they transfer to a rival school.

32
00:05:10,227 --> 00:05:12,062
Why?

33
00:05:12,187 --> 00:05:15,357
Well, 'cause at the end of the season,
nobody wants to be on TV

34
00:05:15,440 --> 00:05:18,485
going, "We're number six, baby.
We're number six."

35
00:05:19,736 --> 00:05:22,406
Well, you asked.

36
00:05:25,659 --> 00:05:27,953
Just had to go there, didn't you?

37
00:05:30,747 --> 00:05:34,126
- Did Darren switch to Tucker?
- We'll talk about it in a minute.

38
00:05:34,251 --> 00:05:36,670
- So it's true?
- We'll talk about it in a minute.

39
00:05:36,753 --> 00:05:38,630
Huddle up.

40
00:05:38,755 --> 00:05:42,176
Coach, is it true
that Darren transferred to Tucker?

41
00:05:45,095 --> 00:05:48,390
I got word this morning
that Darren did transfer to Tucker.

42
00:05:48,515 --> 00:05:52,436
- There goes the season.
- The season will be whatever we make it.

43
00:05:52,519 --> 00:05:55,355
Who's gonna take his place?
He scored a third of our points.

44
00:05:55,439 --> 00:05:58,734
You let me worry about that.
We're not starting as if it's doomsday.

45
00:05:58,859 --> 00:06:01,195
- Nobody's irreplaceable.
- Darren is.

46
00:06:01,278 --> 00:06:04,364
Darren is not. There's more
to a good football team than a running back.

47
00:06:04,448 --> 00:06:07,284
If anything, this ought to push you
to take up the slack.

48
00:06:07,409 --> 00:06:10,078
Stop worrying about Darren.
Start your drills.

49
00:06:10,204 --> 00:06:15,250
- We got a game to play this Friday night.
- Let's go, Shiloh. Come on. Let's go.

50
00:06:41,151 --> 00:06:43,487
Why'd you park all the way out there?

51
00:06:43,612 --> 00:06:45,697
Had to. It died again.

52
00:06:45,822 --> 00:06:47,783
Why don't we get a new battery?

53
00:06:47,908 --> 00:06:51,245
I'll get Brady to help me tomorrow.
I don't wanna think about it now.

54
00:06:51,328 --> 00:06:54,456
- Do you want me to take a look at it for you?
- Stop it.

55
00:06:57,751 --> 00:06:58,794
Oh, sweetheart...

56
00:06:58,919 --> 00:07:02,548
I don't know what that smell is.
I've scrubbed everything I can.

57
00:07:02,673 --> 00:07:05,968
- It's terrible.
- I know it is, but what else can I do?

58
00:07:06,051 --> 00:07:08,011
I don't know where it's coming from.

59
00:07:08,136 --> 00:07:10,264
This day stunk. Why shouldn't my house?

60
00:07:10,347 --> 00:07:13,725
- What do you mean?
- Darren transferred to Tucker.

61
00:07:13,851 --> 00:07:15,978
What? He did not.

62
00:07:16,103 --> 00:07:19,523
Yep. Came by and got his papers,
didn't even say goodbye.

63
00:07:19,648 --> 00:07:21,942
- Why?
- Why do you think?

64
00:07:22,025 --> 00:07:24,528
Didn't see a chance of winning
at Shiloh.

65
00:07:24,611 --> 00:07:27,865
But it ain't like Tucker's
gonna guarantee him a scholarship.

66
00:07:27,990 --> 00:07:31,660
- I bet the boys are frustrated.
- More than you know.

67
00:07:48,552 --> 00:07:51,346
I meant to throw that away.

68
00:07:51,471 --> 00:07:54,057
Did you think you were pregnant?

69
00:07:54,183 --> 00:07:59,146
I don't know. I just wanna be pregnant
so bad that my mind plays tricks on me.

70
00:08:09,907 --> 00:08:13,827
You know, it's been four years
since we started trying.

71
00:08:15,078 --> 00:08:18,207
Would you be opposed
to me going to see a specialist?

72
00:08:20,042 --> 00:08:21,001
No.

73
00:08:21,126 --> 00:08:23,754
I'd just like to know what she says.

74
00:08:25,923 --> 00:08:27,925
OK.

75
00:08:29,551 --> 00:08:31,929
I thought we were having
spaghetti tonight.

76
00:08:32,054 --> 00:08:34,014
Stove's not working.

77
00:08:34,097 --> 00:08:36,683
You are kidding me.

78
00:08:37,559 --> 00:08:40,938
So we got a leak in the back room,
the dryer only works half the time,

79
00:08:41,063 --> 00:08:44,775
the car's dying on us
and now the stove's broken.

80
00:08:44,900 --> 00:08:46,860
That's about right.

81
00:08:46,944 --> 00:08:49,071
No wonder I'm losing my hair.

82
00:08:50,822 --> 00:08:52,449
I love you.

83
00:09:00,582 --> 00:09:05,754
<i>And now your Georgia Sports Break</i>
<i>with Alicia Houston.</i>

84
00:09:05,879 --> 00:09:09,883
The Richland Giants start football practice
as the new school year gets under way.

85
00:09:09,967 --> 00:09:13,804
The team will be defending a three-year
GISA state championship run.

86
00:09:13,929 --> 00:09:15,973
Now they prepare to fight for a fourth.

87
00:09:16,098 --> 00:09:18,976
I'm here with head coach Bobby Lee Duke
of the Giants.

88
00:09:19,059 --> 00:09:21,186
How does this year look for the team?

89
00:09:21,311 --> 00:09:25,065
Alice, we've grown real fond
of the state title.

90
00:09:25,148 --> 00:09:27,651
And we don't see any reason
to give it up this year.

91
00:09:27,776 --> 00:09:31,572
I've got most of my starters coming back
and I've got a strong bench.

92
00:09:31,655 --> 00:09:33,740
So I've only got one thing to say:

93
00:09:33,824 --> 00:09:38,161
get off the tracks,
'cause the freight train's coming.

94
00:11:04,039 --> 00:11:08,460
I hope that's not a sign of the way
the rest of the season's gonna go, Coach.

95
00:11:08,585 --> 00:11:11,296
- Why did he have to say that?
- Just let it go.

96
00:11:11,421 --> 00:11:13,048
I hate this car.

97
00:11:13,131 --> 00:11:15,759
Let's find somebody with jumper cables
and let's go home.

98
00:11:15,884 --> 00:11:19,429
It's bad enough you lose your first game.
Now I can't even start my own car.

99
00:11:19,555 --> 00:11:23,475
This happens to everybody.
Don't be embarrassed about it.

100
00:12:06,810 --> 00:12:11,648
- Grant, I wasn't that embarrassed.
- Then why did you hide?

101
00:12:11,773 --> 00:12:13,942
Why does this house
have to stink so bad?

102
00:12:14,026 --> 00:12:17,613
You'll get used to it
after a couple of hours.

103
00:12:17,738 --> 00:12:20,324
Honey, we gotta do something
about the car.

104
00:12:20,449 --> 00:12:23,327
The only thing it does faithfully for us
is break down.

105
00:12:23,452 --> 00:12:25,245
That's about right.

106
00:12:25,329 --> 00:12:29,541
Would it not be better
just to get a small new car?

107
00:12:29,666 --> 00:12:32,419
- You know we can't afford that.
- How do other people do it?

108
00:12:32,503 --> 00:12:35,339
Other people make
more than 24,000 a year.

109
00:12:35,464 --> 00:12:37,424
You make 6,000. That takes us to 30.

110
00:12:37,508 --> 00:12:40,093
Enough to help us
with repairs occasionally,

111
00:12:40,177 --> 00:12:42,513
not with a new car payment.

112
00:12:42,638 --> 00:12:46,308
Besides, there's other bills
we don't normally have to pay.

113
00:12:46,433 --> 00:12:49,770
- Like what?
- Like my doctor bill.

114
00:12:51,522 --> 00:12:53,815
You saw her today?

115
00:12:54,691 --> 00:12:57,653
- What did she say?
- She said that I'm fine.

116
00:12:57,736 --> 00:13:02,950
My numbers are normal and she saw
nothing that gave her concern.

117
00:13:03,033 --> 00:13:06,578
- That's good.
- It doesn't mean the problem is with you.

118
00:13:06,703 --> 00:13:11,333
- What else could it mean?
- We just may not have given it enough time.

119
00:13:11,458 --> 00:13:13,502
Four years?

120
00:13:15,504 --> 00:13:18,465
Are you still hoping we'll have a baby?

121
00:13:19,883 --> 00:13:24,054
- You know I am.
- Me too.

122
00:13:24,179 --> 00:13:28,058
I catch myself thinking about it
more and more.

123
00:13:28,183 --> 00:13:32,980
Don't you wanna know
if something's preventing it?

124
00:13:35,524 --> 00:13:38,527
Are you afraid of getting checked out?

125
00:13:38,652 --> 00:13:40,863
Yes.

126
00:13:40,946 --> 00:13:45,284
Grant, I'm still clinging to a hope

127
00:13:45,409 --> 00:13:47,911
that one day we'll have children.

128
00:13:50,873 --> 00:13:55,252
I imagine 'em running in this house.

129
00:13:55,335 --> 00:13:58,213
I hear 'em playing in the backyard

130
00:13:58,297 --> 00:14:02,885
or running to our bed in a thunderstorm.

131
00:14:04,887 --> 00:14:08,056
And I think about reading 'em stories

132
00:14:09,725 --> 00:14:12,144
and teaching 'em songs.

133
00:14:15,314 --> 00:14:17,608
And I just keep thinking

134
00:14:20,235 --> 00:14:26,450
how can I miss someone so much
that I have never met?

135
00:14:31,205 --> 00:14:33,582
I'll go.

136
00:14:41,715 --> 00:14:43,342
Stanley.

137
00:14:44,301 --> 00:14:46,261
Stanley.

138
00:14:47,179 --> 00:14:51,016
Stanley, do you wanna tell me
what you're doing on the top of my desk?

139
00:14:52,059 --> 00:14:53,268
No.

140
00:14:53,393 --> 00:14:57,147
Do you have any idea
how you got on top of my desk?

141
00:14:57,272 --> 00:14:58,232
No.

142
00:14:58,315 --> 00:15:00,901
I suggest you get down immediately.

143
00:15:09,576 --> 00:15:13,163
You two can tell Coach Taylor
that you're late for practice today

144
00:15:13,288 --> 00:15:15,457
because you've been
sitting in detention.

145
00:15:15,582 --> 00:15:17,626
Come on. That was some serious humor.

146
00:15:17,709 --> 00:15:21,964
I'll get serious about your humor
when you get serious about your studies.

147
00:15:24,675 --> 00:15:26,677
55?

148
00:15:26,802 --> 00:15:32,558
Well, if you wanna announce your grade
to the entire class, you go right ahead.

149
00:15:32,683 --> 00:15:34,726
57.

150
00:15:37,771 --> 00:15:40,691
So basically we got
the toughest schedule we ever had

151
00:15:40,774 --> 00:15:43,110
and less talent than we ever had.

152
00:15:43,193 --> 00:15:47,406
At least we got Dewey County on Friday
night. That'll be a pretty easy win.

153
00:15:48,532 --> 00:15:52,494
- I'm concerned it might be our only win.
- We'll pull three or four out.

154
00:15:52,619 --> 00:15:55,539
That'll give us another average season.

155
00:15:55,664 --> 00:15:57,833
I'm so sick of average seasons.

156
00:15:59,459 --> 00:16:01,753
- I gotta go.
- Where are you going?

157
00:16:01,879 --> 00:16:04,506
- Got a doctor's appointment.
- For what?

158
00:16:04,631 --> 00:16:06,842
- I have a doctor's appointment.
- For what?

159
00:16:06,925 --> 00:16:11,180
Leave the man alone.
He don't have to tell you.

160
00:16:11,263 --> 00:16:13,515
So what's wrong with you, man?

161
00:16:13,599 --> 00:16:16,059
I'll be back in a couple of hours.

162
00:16:18,353 --> 00:16:21,273
Now look what you did.
You done made him mad.

163
00:16:21,398 --> 00:16:23,692
Me? You're the one that made him mad.

164
00:16:23,817 --> 00:16:27,404
No, not me.
Besides, I know where he's going.

165
00:16:27,529 --> 00:16:30,949
- Where?
- He's going to the hair doctor.

166
00:16:31,074 --> 00:16:35,537
The man is going bald. You hadn't
noticed that underdeveloped region?

167
00:16:35,662 --> 00:16:37,289
You're one to talk, Slick.

168
00:16:37,414 --> 00:16:41,210
See, when a black man goes bald,
he still looks good.

169
00:16:41,293 --> 00:16:46,173
Look at Michael Jordan,
George Foreman, Samuel L. Jackson.

170
00:16:46,256 --> 00:16:49,843
Classy-looking brothers.
Who you got? Kojak?

171
00:16:50,886 --> 00:16:53,639
Yeah, Coach gonna get him some plugs.

172
00:16:54,556 --> 00:16:58,519
- Grant would not get plugs.
- Don't laugh. You next.

173
00:17:22,084 --> 00:17:24,461
Your soccer skills
get better every year, son.

174
00:17:24,586 --> 00:17:28,090
It doesn't matter. Shiloh doesn't have
a soccer team. They play football.

175
00:17:28,215 --> 00:17:30,884
So? Why not kick for the football team?

176
00:17:30,968 --> 00:17:33,011
They've already got a good kicker.

177
00:17:33,136 --> 00:17:35,264
I'm sure they wouldn't mind
having two.

178
00:17:35,389 --> 00:17:39,101
Dad, I'm too small. I really
just don't feel like getting killed.

179
00:17:40,185 --> 00:17:42,229
Are you saying you're not interested

180
00:17:42,312 --> 00:17:45,065
or you'd like to try out
but you're afraid?

181
00:17:45,148 --> 00:17:47,109
What if I don't even make the team?

182
00:17:47,192 --> 00:17:50,028
Well, you're already not on the team.

183
00:17:50,153 --> 00:17:53,323
You can't get any more not on the team
than you are right now.

184
00:17:53,448 --> 00:17:57,160
- OK, Dad.
- David, you can't be afraid of failure.

185
00:17:57,286 --> 00:18:00,163
Everyone fails at some point.

186
00:18:00,247 --> 00:18:03,458
So you think I should try out
for the football team?

187
00:18:03,584 --> 00:18:08,088
Well, if you're waiting around
for soccer, it ain't gonna happen.

188
00:18:17,681 --> 00:18:21,643
- Coach Owens, have you got a minute?
- Yeah.

189
00:18:21,727 --> 00:18:25,689
Look, some of the men have been talking.

190
00:18:25,814 --> 00:18:28,984
We wanna see this school succeed
with our football program.

191
00:18:29,109 --> 00:18:31,153
I know you feel the same way, too.

192
00:18:31,236 --> 00:18:37,034
But, frankly, we don't ever see that
happening while Coach Taylor is here.

193
00:18:37,159 --> 00:18:39,494
You know we're in a rebuilding season.

194
00:18:39,578 --> 00:18:44,541
Look, I know he's a fine man and all,
but he's had six years here

195
00:18:44,625 --> 00:18:47,669
and nothing significant
to even show for it.

196
00:18:47,753 --> 00:18:50,797
I honestly believe
you would make a better head coach.

197
00:18:58,847 --> 00:19:02,559
Some of us have requested
a meeting with Mr. Ryker.

198
00:19:02,684 --> 00:19:08,106
If you would just support us, I really
believe this could go a lot easier.

199
00:19:08,232 --> 00:19:10,234
Mr. Pervis, I don't know.

200
00:19:10,359 --> 00:19:12,903
Look, it's not like
we're trying to hurt the guy.

201
00:19:13,028 --> 00:19:16,365
What we're doing
is for the benefit of the school.

202
00:19:16,490 --> 00:19:19,952
You just think about it.

203
00:19:22,955 --> 00:19:24,915
Good hustle, Casey.

204
00:19:28,585 --> 00:19:30,879
- What was that about?
- What?

205
00:19:32,256 --> 00:19:35,300
- Alvin Pervis.
- We were just talking.

206
00:19:36,844 --> 00:19:38,804
Everything all right?

207
00:19:38,929 --> 00:19:41,223
- Yeah.
- Mr. Taylor.

208
00:19:42,516 --> 00:19:43,684
Yes.

209
00:19:44,685 --> 00:19:48,605
I'm Larry Childers.
This is my son David. He's a junior.

210
00:19:48,689 --> 00:19:51,692
- We're new to the school.
- Good to meet you. What can I do for you?

211
00:19:51,775 --> 00:19:56,238
I just wanted to introduce myself to you
and David wanted to try out for the team.

212
00:19:56,321 --> 00:19:59,324
- You a football player?
- I've always played soccer.

213
00:19:59,449 --> 00:20:02,911
- I figured I could try out as a kicker.
- I've got a pretty good kicker,

214
00:20:03,036 --> 00:20:07,040
but I don't mind letting you try out.
Jonathan, come here.

215
00:20:07,124 --> 00:20:10,669
This is Jonathan. He holds
for our main kicker, Joshua Webster.

216
00:20:10,794 --> 00:20:14,715
Jonathan, this is David Childers.
He wants to try out as a kicker.

217
00:20:14,798 --> 00:20:18,802
- Why don't you two go and try a few kicks?
- All right, sure.

218
00:20:18,927 --> 00:20:22,389
Thank you, sir. I'll just hang around
till practice is over.

219
00:20:22,514 --> 00:20:25,225
No problem. Good to meet you.

220
00:20:25,475 --> 00:20:27,269
Y'all just move here?

221
00:20:27,394 --> 00:20:31,440
Yeah, from Athens. My dad got a job
teaching at the college.

222
00:20:31,523 --> 00:20:32,900
That's cool.

223
00:20:32,983 --> 00:20:37,321
I'm used to kicking soccer balls,
but I thought I could at least try out.

224
00:20:37,446 --> 00:20:40,449
Josh is a pretty good kicker,
but he's also a receiver.

225
00:20:40,574 --> 00:20:44,036
I think he likes that
better than kicking. Here you go.

226
00:20:56,173 --> 00:20:58,133
I'm sorry.

227
00:20:59,843 --> 00:21:01,637
I'm sorry.

228
00:21:03,597 --> 00:21:05,557
I'm sorry.

229
00:21:09,645 --> 00:21:11,605
- Sorry about that.
- It's all right.

230
00:21:17,861 --> 00:21:20,614
- Hey, watch it.
- Sorry.

231
00:21:32,584 --> 00:21:34,211
Matt.

232
00:21:34,878 --> 00:21:36,839
Matt.

233
00:21:39,174 --> 00:21:41,885
- Let's go.
- I'm going with Brock for a while.

234
00:21:42,010 --> 00:21:44,179
- Not tonight. You're coming home.
- Why?

235
00:21:44,263 --> 00:21:48,058
- Don't argue with me. Let's go.
- No, Dad. I'll be home later.

236
00:21:48,183 --> 00:21:49,434
Matt.

237
00:22:07,995 --> 00:22:11,540
That old man still come every week
to pray in the hallway?

238
00:22:11,623 --> 00:22:15,460
Mr. Bridges. Prays for the students
as he passes their locker.

239
00:22:16,503 --> 00:22:21,425
- How long has he been doing that?
- Praying for revival since before I got here.

240
00:22:21,550 --> 00:22:26,180
Lord knows we need it. Apathy in the
school's as bad as our football record.

241
00:22:26,263 --> 00:22:30,350
That reminds me. I think you should go ahead
and let David Childers on the team.

242
00:22:32,269 --> 00:22:36,315
- You see something there?
- He's just used to playing soccer.

243
00:22:36,440 --> 00:22:39,234
He ain't that strong,
but he shows promise.

244
00:22:41,111 --> 00:22:43,572
All right. I'll give him a shot.

245
00:22:56,293 --> 00:22:58,295
One, two, hit!

246
00:23:07,304 --> 00:23:10,599
What are you doing?
Let's stay in the game!

247
00:23:17,147 --> 00:23:18,982
No! No!

248
00:23:23,904 --> 00:23:27,491
Will someone tell me
how we lost to Dewey County 21 to 7?

249
00:23:28,325 --> 00:23:30,452
21 to 7!

250
00:23:30,536 --> 00:23:34,790
Dewey County hasn't beaten Shiloh
since you were in kindergarten!

251
00:23:34,915 --> 00:23:39,920
I don't know what you call that junk
out there, but it sure wasn't football.

252
00:23:40,003 --> 00:23:43,006
Nine dropped passes,
four fumbles, three interceptions.

253
00:23:43,090 --> 00:23:45,425
Their defense
scored most of their points!

254
00:23:45,509 --> 00:23:48,345
You gave the game away!

255
00:23:48,470 --> 00:23:52,432
You can't win football games
if you don't play together as a team.

256
00:23:52,558 --> 00:23:56,645
You can't win when you're more concerned
about what you're doing afterwards!

257
00:23:56,728 --> 00:24:02,192
And you can't learn the plays when you miss
practice 'cause you're sittin' in detention.

258
00:24:03,026 --> 00:24:05,821
I'm sick of the apathy on this team.

259
00:24:05,904 --> 00:24:10,075
If we're not here to win football games,
then why are we here?

260
00:24:15,998 --> 00:24:18,166
So, do you agree with him?

261
00:24:18,250 --> 00:24:21,712
I don't know. I guess.

262
00:24:21,795 --> 00:24:25,340
Only a few guys on the team
really seem to care.

263
00:24:25,424 --> 00:24:27,676
So are you ready to play in the game?

264
00:24:27,801 --> 00:24:31,221
I don't know why they would use me
when they've got Joshua Webster.

265
00:24:31,346 --> 00:24:34,016
He can kick a 45-yard field goal.

266
00:24:34,099 --> 00:24:35,726
I bet you could too.

267
00:24:35,851 --> 00:24:39,479
Dad, I can barely kick
a 35-yard field goal.

268
00:24:39,563 --> 00:24:42,733
At the end of the game,
kind of glad I didn't play.

269
00:24:42,858 --> 00:24:45,652
That way, I can't mess up.

270
00:24:45,736 --> 00:24:49,656
- That's fear, son.
- I just don't wanna embarrass the team.

271
00:24:50,741 --> 00:24:54,828
David, I've asked God
since you were a baby

272
00:24:54,912 --> 00:24:58,332
that he would show how strong he is
in your life

273
00:24:58,415 --> 00:25:02,169
and that through you
people would see how good he is.

274
00:25:03,212 --> 00:25:06,798
Then why would he make me
so small and weak?

275
00:25:06,924 --> 00:25:09,009
To show how mighty he is.

276
00:25:11,762 --> 00:25:15,182
Why don't we get washed up for dinner?
We can finish this later.

277
00:25:15,265 --> 00:25:17,267
All right.

278
00:26:10,320 --> 00:26:12,406
Dad.

279
00:26:15,409 --> 00:26:17,494
OK. I'm OK.

280
00:26:17,619 --> 00:26:20,163
- What were you doing?
- You missed a spot up there.

281
00:26:20,289 --> 00:26:22,624
Thought I could get it for you.

282
00:26:22,749 --> 00:26:25,377
I guess I got a little too ambitious.

283
00:26:25,502 --> 00:26:28,463
I was just trying to take a swing at it.

284
00:26:40,851 --> 00:26:43,395
So, what does that mean?

285
00:26:43,520 --> 00:26:47,566
Is there a procedure?
What are my options?

286
00:26:48,692 --> 00:26:52,696
Grant, first you need you realize
this is a fairly common problem for men.

287
00:26:52,821 --> 00:26:57,534
Thousands of couples are unable
to have children. You do have options.

288
00:26:57,659 --> 00:27:00,662
Although there's only
a 10% chance of success,

289
00:27:00,787 --> 00:27:03,832
many couples have tried
in vitro fertilization.

290
00:27:03,957 --> 00:27:08,879
- We can't afford that.
- The other option is to adopt a child.

291
00:27:09,004 --> 00:27:11,673
But it's about as expensive either way.

292
00:27:11,757 --> 00:27:16,428
If you're interested, I'll put you
in touch with the local agency.

293
00:27:16,553 --> 00:27:19,973
I realize this is difficult
for you to hear,

294
00:27:20,057 --> 00:27:22,559
but you and your wife can
make the best decision

295
00:27:22,684 --> 00:27:25,270
now that you know where you are.

296
00:27:39,368 --> 00:27:42,037
Sorry. I didn't realize
anybody was still here.

297
00:27:42,120 --> 00:27:45,457
- Hey, Steve.
- Putting in late hours tonight?

298
00:27:45,582 --> 00:27:49,002
Yeah, I guess so.
I can lock up. You can take off.

299
00:27:49,086 --> 00:27:51,088
All right. Thanks, Coach.

300
00:28:26,123 --> 00:28:28,917
It's about the boys.

301
00:28:29,042 --> 00:28:31,128
I'm not asking you to throw him out.

302
00:28:31,253 --> 00:28:35,632
If Shiloh can invest in a winning coach,
we don't need to settle for second best.

303
00:28:35,757 --> 00:28:38,218
You can let him go
with as much class as you want to.

304
00:28:38,302 --> 00:28:41,763
- Alvin, he's a good man.
- I'm not saying he's not a good man.

305
00:28:41,847 --> 00:28:44,099
I'm saying he's not a good coach.

306
00:28:44,224 --> 00:28:48,228
Come on, Dan. Just look at the facts.
His record speaks for itself.

307
00:28:48,312 --> 00:28:52,232
- We need new leadership.
- I still think he deserves more time.

308
00:28:52,316 --> 00:28:57,112
He's had six years. If he was capable
of winning, he'd have done it by now.

309
00:28:57,196 --> 00:28:59,740
Grant Taylor is not capable of winning.

310
00:28:59,823 --> 00:29:02,910
He doesn't have it in him.
That's the whole point.

311
00:29:02,993 --> 00:29:07,247
I'm just saying I want my son to have
the best football program possible.

312
00:29:07,331 --> 00:29:09,958
My son's got a chance
for a football scholarship

313
00:29:10,042 --> 00:29:12,294
if he's taught by the right coach.

314
00:29:12,419 --> 00:29:14,379
Matt's gonna be a senior next year.

315
00:29:14,505 --> 00:29:17,466
I don't wanna see him
lose this opportunity.

316
00:29:17,549 --> 00:29:22,095
Brady, you're awfully quiet.
What's your take on this?

317
00:29:22,179 --> 00:29:24,681
Honestly, I don't know.

318
00:29:24,765 --> 00:29:29,144
Sometimes I think Grant could do a better job
of building this football program.

319
00:29:29,228 --> 00:29:33,941
But then other times I think he's doing
just as good as anyone else would.

320
00:29:34,024 --> 00:29:36,568
You could do better.

321
00:29:36,693 --> 00:29:38,862
- What we need is a change.
- Now.

322
00:29:38,987 --> 00:29:42,199
We're losing booster support,
game attendance is down,

323
00:29:42,324 --> 00:29:45,869
and from the looks of it
we've already lost this season.

324
00:29:45,994 --> 00:29:49,831
Dan, we've got a weak program
because we've got a weak coach.

325
00:29:49,915 --> 00:29:53,168
He's dead weight.
We need to cut him loose.

326
00:30:05,055 --> 00:30:08,433
Have you been at school all this time?

327
00:30:08,559 --> 00:30:10,185
Yes.

328
00:30:10,310 --> 00:30:14,273
I tried to call you an hour ago.
Is everything all right?

329
00:30:21,154 --> 00:30:23,532
Grant, talk to me.

330
00:30:28,120 --> 00:30:30,581
I don't know where to start.

331
00:30:32,416 --> 00:30:34,376
What's going on?

332
00:30:37,880 --> 00:30:41,425
I was trying to lock up for Steve

333
00:30:41,550 --> 00:30:44,136
and I overheard Dan
meeting with some fathers.

334
00:30:46,597 --> 00:30:49,099
They didn't know I was there.

335
00:30:51,935 --> 00:30:56,064
Brooke, they're pushing him
to get rid of me.

336
00:30:56,148 --> 00:31:01,069
Neil Prater, Alvin Pervis, Luke Rae.

337
00:31:03,030 --> 00:31:08,994
They said I wasn't capable of winning,
called me dead weight.

338
00:31:09,119 --> 00:31:12,331
They can't make Dan fire you.
You've still got support.

339
00:31:12,456 --> 00:31:16,877
You just go get JT and Brady
and see him tomorrow.

340
00:31:16,960 --> 00:31:19,129
Brady was there.

341
00:31:25,761 --> 00:31:28,222
They've just lost confidence in me.

342
00:31:31,016 --> 00:31:36,897
I was so sure I could turn this program
around and I've just sunk it lower.

343
00:31:39,983 --> 00:31:44,279
Brooke, I've tried so hard.
Why can't I win?

344
00:31:44,404 --> 00:31:48,492
You can win.
Stop beating yourself up, Grant.

345
00:31:48,617 --> 00:31:52,037
Brooke, I can't provide you
with a decent home.

346
00:31:52,162 --> 00:31:55,707
I can't provide you with a decent car.

347
00:31:55,832 --> 00:31:58,794
I'm a failing coach
with a losing record.

348
00:32:01,296 --> 00:32:04,508
And I can't give you
the children you want.

349
00:32:06,009 --> 00:32:07,970
What?

350
00:32:10,264 --> 00:32:12,224
It's me.

351
00:32:13,100 --> 00:32:15,060
Like everything else is me.

352
00:32:17,271 --> 00:32:21,483
We can't have our own children
because of me.

353
00:32:23,026 --> 00:32:27,656
What's God doing?
I mean, why is it so hard?

354
00:32:29,700 --> 00:32:32,828
It's OK, Grant.

355
00:32:33,704 --> 00:32:35,956
It's OK.

356
00:34:10,384 --> 00:34:12,386
I love you, O Lord, my strength."

357
00:34:12,469 --> 00:34:16,765
The Lord is my rock and my fortress,
my deliverer,

358
00:34:16,890 --> 00:34:19,393
my God in whom I trust,

359
00:34:19,476 --> 00:34:24,606
my shield and the horn of my salvation,
my stronghold."

360
00:34:24,731 --> 00:34:28,277
I will call upon the Lord
who is worthy to be praised."

361
00:34:28,402 --> 00:34:31,363
So shall I be saved from my enemies."

362
00:34:33,657 --> 00:34:36,034
Lord Jesus, would you help me?

363
00:34:36,159 --> 00:34:38,120
I need you.

364
00:34:40,122 --> 00:34:42,833
Lord, I feel like
there's giants of fear and failure

365
00:34:42,958 --> 00:34:45,919
just staring down at me
waiting to crush me.

366
00:34:46,003 --> 00:34:48,755
And I don't know how to beat 'em, Lord.

367
00:34:48,839 --> 00:34:51,341
I'm tired of being afraid.

368
00:34:53,343 --> 00:34:57,723
Lord, if you want me
to do something else, show me.

369
00:34:57,848 --> 00:35:02,561
If you don't want me to have children,
so be it.

370
00:35:02,686 --> 00:35:05,314
But you're my guide.

371
00:35:05,397 --> 00:35:07,691
You're on the throne.

372
00:35:09,067 --> 00:35:12,029
You can have
my hopes and my dreams.

373
00:35:14,072 --> 00:35:18,035
Lord, give me something.
Show me something.

374
00:35:46,146 --> 00:35:50,108
If the Lord never gives us children,
will you still love him?

375
00:36:10,754 --> 00:36:12,256
Field-goal unit.

376
00:36:12,381 --> 00:36:16,927
Hold on, Joshua. I wanna give David
a shot at this one. David, come here.

377
00:36:17,052 --> 00:36:19,930
This is your field goal.
Put us on the board.

378
00:36:36,780 --> 00:36:39,032
Hit.

379
00:36:45,581 --> 00:36:48,542
It's all right, man. It's hard.
You'll get it next time.

380
00:37:00,804 --> 00:37:04,016
Dad, I don't even know
why they let me on the team.

381
00:37:04,141 --> 00:37:05,601
Did you do your best, son?

382
00:37:05,684 --> 00:37:08,020
I knew I was gonna miss it
before I kicked it.

383
00:37:08,145 --> 00:37:11,940
Your actions will always
follow your beliefs, David.

384
00:37:12,065 --> 00:37:14,443
Dad, I can't even kick it straight.

385
00:37:14,568 --> 00:37:19,281
And I can't walk. Should I just
stay home and pout about it?

386
00:37:19,364 --> 00:37:23,493
If you accept defeat, David,
then that's what you'll get.

387
00:37:28,707 --> 00:37:31,960
Well, Brady, another fine example

388
00:37:32,085 --> 00:37:35,339
of Grant Taylor's
wonderful coaching abilities.

389
00:37:35,464 --> 00:37:38,675
Look, the kids don't deserve it.
The fans don't deserve it.

390
00:37:38,800 --> 00:37:41,053
When you gonna get
a bellyful of this guy?

391
00:37:41,178 --> 00:37:43,680
What's it gonna take?
You got a chance, man.

392
00:37:43,805 --> 00:37:46,892
You got a chance to step in
and take over this program

393
00:37:47,017 --> 00:37:49,186
and carry it up for a while.

394
00:37:49,311 --> 00:37:51,605
When are you gonna get
sick and tired of it?

395
00:37:51,688 --> 00:37:55,108
You got an opportunity here.
This program's going in the tank.

396
00:37:55,192 --> 00:37:57,194
Ryker's gotta...

397
00:38:12,209 --> 00:38:14,711
Grant, he came to me.

398
00:38:17,840 --> 00:38:20,467
You're not doing anybody any favors
sitting on the fence.

399
00:38:20,551 --> 00:38:23,804
You determine which side
you wanna be on and stay on it.

400
00:38:41,947 --> 00:38:43,907
Mr. Bridges.

401
00:38:45,659 --> 00:38:47,536
Revelation Chapter 3 says:

402
00:38:47,619 --> 00:38:51,123
We serve a God
that opens doors that no one can shut,

403
00:38:51,248 --> 00:38:54,418
and he shuts doors
that no one can open."

404
00:38:54,543 --> 00:39:00,382
He says: 'Behold, I have placed before
you an open door that no one can shut.

405
00:39:00,507 --> 00:39:02,718
'I know you have a little strength,

406
00:39:02,843 --> 00:39:07,055
yet you have kept my word
and have not denied my name."'

407
00:39:08,765 --> 00:39:12,311
Coach Taylor,
the Lord is not through with you yet.

408
00:39:12,436 --> 00:39:14,897
You still have an open door here,

409
00:39:14,980 --> 00:39:19,651
and until the Lord moves you, you're
to bloom right where you're planted.

410
00:39:20,944 --> 00:39:24,364
I just felt led
to come and tell you that today.

411
00:39:37,461 --> 00:39:39,421
Mr. Bridges.

412
00:39:42,090 --> 00:39:44,927
Do you believe
God told you to come tell me that?

413
00:39:45,010 --> 00:39:46,970
I do.

414
00:39:49,014 --> 00:39:52,142
I admit to you I have been struggling.

415
00:39:52,267 --> 00:39:55,103
But I've also been praying.

416
00:39:55,187 --> 00:39:58,982
I just don't see him at work here.

417
00:39:59,107 --> 00:40:04,613
Grant, I heard a story about two farmers
who desperately needed rain.

418
00:40:04,738 --> 00:40:06,949
And both of them prayed for rain,

419
00:40:07,074 --> 00:40:11,453
but only one of them went out
and prepared his fields to receive it.

420
00:40:11,537 --> 00:40:15,916
Which one do you think trusted God
to send the rain?

421
00:40:15,999 --> 00:40:19,503
The one who prepared his fields for it.

422
00:40:19,628 --> 00:40:21,755
Which one are you?

423
00:40:21,839 --> 00:40:24,341
God will send the rain when he's ready.

424
00:40:24,466 --> 00:40:27,886
You need to prepare your field
to receive it.

425
00:41:15,225 --> 00:41:17,686
So this is your new team philosophy?

426
00:41:17,769 --> 00:41:19,730
What do you think?

427
00:41:19,855 --> 00:41:23,358
I think this applies to all of life,
not just football.

428
00:41:23,483 --> 00:41:25,944
Well, that's my point.

429
00:41:27,529 --> 00:41:31,366
10 bucks to the person who can tell me who
won the state championship a decade ago.

430
00:41:31,450 --> 00:41:33,285
- Walker Jennings.
- No.

431
00:41:33,410 --> 00:41:35,537
- North Metro.
- Stop guessing.

432
00:41:35,662 --> 00:41:38,165
You know it or you don't.

433
00:41:38,290 --> 00:41:41,084
- How about five years ago?
- Richland?

434
00:41:41,210 --> 00:41:43,879
That was three years ago.

435
00:41:43,962 --> 00:41:47,049
You can't remember, can you?

436
00:41:47,132 --> 00:41:49,176
Leads me to ask a couple of questions.

437
00:41:50,469 --> 00:41:53,972
- What's the purpose of this team?
- Win ball games.

438
00:41:54,097 --> 00:41:57,518
- Then what?
- We get a trophy. And people talk about us.

439
00:41:57,601 --> 00:41:59,895
Maybe, for a while.

440
00:42:00,020 --> 00:42:02,314
- Then what?
- I don't know.

441
00:42:02,439 --> 00:42:07,444
Get a scholarship, play for college
and coach Little League.

442
00:42:09,154 --> 00:42:12,491
What are you getting at?
You think we're just wasting our time?

443
00:42:12,616 --> 00:42:14,743
If our main goal is to win games,
then yes.

444
00:42:14,868 --> 00:42:18,455
- You don't want us to win games?
- No.

445
00:42:18,580 --> 00:42:21,333
Not if that's our main goal.

446
00:42:21,458 --> 00:42:24,753
Winning football games
is too small a thing to live for.

447
00:42:24,878 --> 00:42:27,422
And I love football as much as anybody.

448
00:42:27,548 --> 00:42:31,760
But even championship trophies will
one day collect dust and be forgotten.

449
00:42:33,679 --> 00:42:36,723
It's just that so far
all this has been about us,

450
00:42:36,849 --> 00:42:40,644
how we can look good,
how we can get the glory.

451
00:42:42,646 --> 00:42:47,901
The more I read this book,
the more I realize life's not about us.

452
00:42:48,819 --> 00:42:51,780
We're not here just to get glory,
make money and die.

453
00:42:51,905 --> 00:42:54,908
The Bible says
that God put us here for him,

454
00:42:55,033 --> 00:42:57,536
to honor him.

455
00:42:57,661 --> 00:43:00,289
Jesus said the most important thing
you could do with your life

456
00:43:00,372 --> 00:43:04,126
is to love God with everything you are
and love others as yourself.

457
00:43:04,251 --> 00:43:08,714
So if we win every game
and we miss that, we've done nothing.

458
00:43:08,839 --> 00:43:11,258
Football then means nothing.

459
00:43:12,176 --> 00:43:15,596
So I'm here to present you
a new team philosophy.

460
00:43:15,679 --> 00:43:19,308
I think that football is just
one of the tools we use to honor God.

461
00:43:19,433 --> 00:43:21,852
So you think God
does care about football?

462
00:43:21,977 --> 00:43:24,605
I think he cares about your faith.

463
00:43:24,688 --> 00:43:26,857
He cares about where your heart is.

464
00:43:26,982 --> 00:43:28,942
If you can live your faith on the football field,

465
00:43:29,026 --> 00:43:32,279
then, yes, God cares
'cause he cares about you.

466
00:43:32,362 --> 00:43:35,532
He sent his son Jesus to die for us
so we could live for him.

467
00:43:35,657 --> 00:43:37,492
That's why we're here.

468
