I'd give my right arm
to hear my son say that to me.

696
00:59:18,684 --> 00:59:22,563
I feel like I'm standing
before a new team tonight.

697
00:59:22,646 --> 00:59:25,899
It's a new day and a new game.

698
00:59:25,983 --> 00:59:30,070
What you've experienced in your hearts
this week will be released on the field.

699
00:59:30,153 --> 00:59:32,739
Stay humble but confident.

700
00:59:33,907 --> 00:59:36,535
Why don't you take this one, Brock?

701
00:59:39,997 --> 00:59:42,666
Lord, we know
our lives are not about football,

702
00:59:42,791 --> 00:59:45,460
but we do thank you
for allowing us to play tonight.

703
00:59:45,586 --> 00:59:47,838
We're gonna give you our best.

704
00:59:47,963 --> 00:59:51,550
If we win, we'll praise you
and if we lose, we'll praise you.

705
00:59:51,633 --> 00:59:55,220
We'll give you all the honor and the glory
for this night. Keep us safe.

706
00:59:55,345 --> 00:59:57,639
- Amen.
- Amen.

707
00:59:57,723 --> 01:00:00,309
All right, guys. Look at me.

708
01:00:00,434 --> 01:00:02,978
Play hard, have fun.

709
01:00:09,651 --> 01:00:11,528
Hit.

710
01:01:09,127 --> 01:01:11,255
In the Old Testament,
Nehemiah had the task of

711
01:01:11,380 --> 01:01:13,966
building a wall around his city
for protection.

712
01:01:14,091 --> 01:01:17,177
But he didn't have enough people
or resources or time.

713
01:01:17,261 --> 01:01:20,305
Because each person worked on the wall
in front of their house,

714
01:01:20,430 --> 01:01:23,642
they got it done in record time.
That's what you're gonna do.

715
01:01:23,725 --> 01:01:27,896
On defense you have to resolve
nothing gets by you as an individual,

716
01:01:27,980 --> 01:01:29,982
nothing gets by us as a team.

717
01:01:30,107 --> 01:01:32,568
I need you to build me a stone wall.

718
01:02:20,157 --> 01:02:22,075
Let's go. Let's go.

719
01:02:22,159 --> 01:02:24,620
Run through
like you're throwing yourself.

720
01:02:25,412 --> 01:02:29,666
Come on. Hit somebody! I wanna see
some hitting. I wanna see some hitting.

721
01:02:29,791 --> 01:02:33,504
Dig those feet. Come on, you ain't
on my team yet. You ain't on my defense.

722
01:02:33,629 --> 01:02:37,174
You gotta dig those feet.
All right, Prater. Get in there, boy.

723
01:02:37,299 --> 01:02:39,301
Hit him a little harder than that.

724
01:02:39,426 --> 01:02:42,387
This ain't ballet practice.
This is football practice.

725
01:03:12,459 --> 01:03:14,670
David.

726
01:03:14,795 --> 01:03:15,963
David.

727
01:03:32,896 --> 01:03:37,943
Double sweep pitch lift. Pro 45 fix.
Man, even a 26 Powerhouse.

728
01:03:38,068 --> 01:03:41,154
- Man, these are some good plays.
- We're gonna run 'em.

729
01:03:41,238 --> 01:03:44,199
We got all type of potential
on this sheet. When?

730
01:03:44,283 --> 01:03:45,868
We're gonna run 'em, I promise.

731
01:03:45,993 --> 01:03:50,998
See, you always tell me you're gonna
run 'em. You don't wanna run my plays.

732
01:03:52,332 --> 01:03:53,792
Where's my car?

733
01:03:53,917 --> 01:03:57,462
- Where'd you park it?
- Right here.

734
01:03:57,588 --> 01:04:01,008
You sure?
'Cause there ain't no way it got stolen.

735
01:04:01,133 --> 01:04:03,385
You couldn't pay nobody
to steal your car.

736
01:04:03,510 --> 01:04:07,139
- Did the boys do something with it?
- I don't know.

737
01:04:07,264 --> 01:04:10,225
Hey, man,
there's a note on this truck for you.

738
01:04:11,268 --> 01:04:14,188
- What does it say?
- Let's see.

739
01:04:14,271 --> 01:04:17,608
It says "Grant Taylor,
the impact you made on our school

740
01:04:17,733 --> 01:04:19,902
means more to us
than you'll ever know.

741
01:04:20,027 --> 01:04:22,529
The Lord has used you
to meet a need in our lives

742
01:04:22,613 --> 01:04:24,615
and now we want
to meet a need in yours.

743
01:04:24,698 --> 01:04:28,243
You'll find the title
of this new truck in your name.

744
01:04:28,368 --> 01:04:31,663
Please accept it
as our way of saying thank you."

745
01:04:35,000 --> 01:04:37,503
Somebody done gave you a truck?

746
01:04:44,218 --> 01:04:46,678
Man, this title got your name on it.

747
01:04:55,646 --> 01:04:58,106
You got to be kidding me.

748
01:05:02,778 --> 01:05:06,782
Grant Taylor,
somebody done gave you a new truck.

749
01:05:08,992 --> 01:05:11,286
This is my truck?

750
01:05:27,553 --> 01:05:30,055
Is this just 'cause you head coach?

751
01:05:30,180 --> 01:05:32,933
'Cause I'm assistant coach.

752
01:05:33,016 --> 01:05:36,311
You'd think I'd get a moped
out of this or something.

753
01:05:44,778 --> 01:05:48,156
Oh, Lord, you've given me a truck.

754
01:05:48,282 --> 01:05:52,202
Well, it's your truck. Drive it.

755
01:05:55,873 --> 01:05:58,125
Not a word to anyone.

756
01:05:58,208 --> 01:06:00,419
Yes, sir.

757
01:06:07,926 --> 01:06:10,846
That right.
No more jumper cables.

758
01:06:17,519 --> 01:06:19,605
Brock. Brock.

759
01:06:19,730 --> 01:06:23,650
- You watch him. You watch him.
- Sure.

760
01:06:38,248 --> 01:06:40,459
- Go.
- Go. Go.

761
01:07:39,643 --> 01:07:41,937
- Yes, sir? Can I help you?
- Please.

762
01:07:42,062 --> 01:07:45,941
I'd like to buy a nice bouquet
of wild flowers for my wife.

763
01:07:46,024 --> 01:07:48,485
I see.
That's awfully sweet of you.

764
01:07:48,610 --> 01:07:52,447
Oh, yes. I've got a special evening
in mind for her tonight.

765
01:07:52,531 --> 01:07:55,367
In that case, you need a card
to go with those flowers.

766
01:07:55,492 --> 01:08:00,247
I've got the perfect one. I'm gonna give
it to her at her favorite restaurant.

767
01:08:00,330 --> 01:08:03,041
Really? I'm sure she'll be happy.

768
01:08:03,166 --> 01:08:08,964
She will. So I need your nicest,
largest flowers, and money's no object.

769
01:08:10,340 --> 01:08:14,303
- You see, I got a raise today.
- You did?

770
01:08:14,428 --> 01:08:17,764
- $6,000.
- Are you serious?

771
01:08:17,848 --> 01:08:20,142
That's the way my wife's gonna respond.

772
01:08:20,267 --> 01:08:21,894
Grant.

773
01:08:22,352 --> 01:08:24,271
Grant.

774
01:08:24,354 --> 01:08:28,358
- That's awesome.
- You sure got friendly service here.

775
01:08:35,115 --> 01:08:38,577
Hello again. This is Lane Lavarre,
along with Dale Hansen,

776
01:08:38,702 --> 01:08:41,622
coming to you tonight
from Princeton Heights Academy,

777
01:08:41,705 --> 01:08:45,125
the site of tonight's opening round
of the GISA football playoffs.

778
01:08:45,209 --> 01:08:47,085
For the first time in a decade,

779
01:08:47,211 --> 01:08:49,796
the Shiloh Eagles
are in postseason play.

780
01:08:49,880 --> 01:08:52,382
Coach Grant Taylor's
gonna have his hands full

781
01:08:52,508 --> 01:08:56,887
as he takes on the Panthers,
who haven't lost a game all season.

782
01:08:57,012 --> 01:09:00,390
Huddle up. Stay sharp, stay focused,
play hard and honor God.

783
01:09:00,516 --> 01:09:02,976
- Eagles on three. One, two, three.
- Eagles.

784
01:09:40,222 --> 01:09:42,182
<i>So, after an impressive record,</i>

785
01:09:42,266 --> 01:09:46,436
<i>the Shiloh Eagles fall short tonight</i>
<i>in the first round of the GISA playoffs.</i>

786
01:09:46,562 --> 01:09:50,899
28 to 10, the Princeton Heights Panthers
take it to the Shiloh Eagles.

787
01:09:52,442 --> 01:09:55,237
I knew we were gonna get killed tonight.

788
01:10:08,166 --> 01:10:11,837
Your effort was good tonight.
You've got nothing to be ashamed of.

789
01:10:16,216 --> 01:10:21,096
You played hard. The Shilohs
had their best season in a long time.

790
01:10:21,221 --> 01:10:23,557
God's been good to us this year.

791
01:10:30,355 --> 01:10:32,566
Guys, Coach is right.

792
01:10:32,649 --> 01:10:36,528
We gotta praise God when we win
and praise him when we lose.

793
01:10:39,781 --> 01:10:42,075
Let's take a knee.

794
01:10:57,257 --> 01:10:59,218
Hey.

795
01:11:04,014 --> 01:11:08,310
I wish by some miracle
we could have won tonight.

796
01:11:08,435 --> 01:11:12,397
They worked too hard
to walk away with their heads down.

797
01:11:14,274 --> 01:11:18,237
I was hoping God would give us
just one win in the playoffs.

798
01:11:21,865 --> 01:11:23,825
They deserved it.

799
01:11:31,708 --> 01:11:36,213
If you'd told me two months ago we'd
play Princeton Heights in the playoffs,

800
01:11:36,338 --> 01:11:38,173
I would not have believed you.

801
01:11:38,257 --> 01:11:42,886
If you'd told me our school was having
a revival, I wouldn't have believed you.

802
01:11:43,011 --> 01:11:45,472
- This ain't been a bad year.
- Got all the jerseys?

803
01:11:45,556 --> 01:11:50,227
All 32 of 'em. But I ain't ready to put
'em up. I'm ready to go another round.

804
01:11:50,352 --> 01:11:53,313
You and me both.
Part of me wanted to get to state.

805
01:11:53,438 --> 01:11:57,776
- To state? Grant, are you serious?
- Why not? As hard as they worked?

806
01:11:57,901 --> 01:12:00,863
Working hard is one thing,
but to take this team to state?

807
01:12:00,946 --> 01:12:04,366
- That'd take an act of God.
- Has he not been acting already?

808
01:12:04,449 --> 01:12:08,328
He has, but do you know who's gonna
be waiting for whoever gets to state?

809
01:12:08,412 --> 01:12:10,914
- The Richland Giants.
- That's right.

810
01:12:11,039 --> 01:12:13,876
Bobby Lee Duke will be there
with his 85 players

811
01:12:13,959 --> 01:12:18,130
ready to spank whoever made it
to the state playoffs to kingdom come.

812
01:12:18,255 --> 01:12:21,049
- I'm not afraid.
- I know you're not afraid.

813
01:12:21,175 --> 01:12:22,801
'Cause you ain't going.

814
01:12:22,926 --> 01:12:25,304
By the way,
some man called looking for you.

815
01:12:25,429 --> 01:12:28,974
- Who?
- Stan Shultz.

816
01:12:29,099 --> 01:12:31,518
- Stan Shultz?
- Yeah.

817
01:12:31,602 --> 01:12:36,315
- Stan Shultz. That the cartoonist?
- That's Charles Schulz.

818
01:12:36,440 --> 01:12:39,443
Charles Schulz was that man
that flew across the ocean

819
01:12:39,568 --> 01:12:41,320
in the <i>Spirit of St. Andrew</i>.

820
01:12:41,445 --> 01:12:44,656
That's Charles Lindbergh,
and it was the <i>Spirit of St. Louis</i>.

821
01:12:44,781 --> 01:12:47,492
- Lindbergh is a cheese.
- Limburger's the cheese.

822
01:12:47,618 --> 01:12:48,911
Lindbergh's the man.

823
01:12:49,036 --> 01:12:53,290
Lindbergh was that blimp that blew up
and killed all them people.

824
01:12:54,833 --> 01:12:57,211
That's the <i>Hindenburg</i>.

825
01:13:00,130 --> 01:13:03,091
No, Hindenburg
is where you go skiing in Tennessee.

826
01:13:03,175 --> 01:13:05,844
- That's Gatlinburg.
- Gatlinburg...

827
01:13:05,969 --> 01:13:09,348
You mean like the country music group,
the Gatlinburg Brothers?

828
01:13:11,308 --> 01:13:13,602
You guys are crazy.

829
01:13:15,312 --> 01:13:17,397
Grant Taylor.

830
01:13:17,523 --> 01:13:21,860
Well, Mr. Shultz,
I was told you were looking for me.

831
01:13:21,985 --> 01:13:25,781
Yes. Am I sitting down?
Why do you ask?

832
01:13:28,784 --> 01:13:30,994
Hey, Coach, what's going on here?

833
01:13:31,119 --> 01:13:34,081
- Coach is on his way to let us know.
- All right.

834
01:13:37,000 --> 01:13:39,002
Bring it in.

835
01:13:44,091 --> 01:13:48,095
I want you to know I serve a big God
and he can do whatever he wants to do.

836
01:13:48,220 --> 01:13:50,848
He can open what he wants to
and shut what he wants to.

837
01:13:50,973 --> 01:13:55,310
A team that plays for his honor
and glory will have his blessings.

838
01:13:55,394 --> 01:13:59,606
Unlike those who try to cheat their way
to the top, like Princeton Heights did

839
01:13:59,690 --> 01:14:02,317
when they played
two ineligible 19-year-olds.

840
01:14:02,401 --> 01:14:05,445
They have been disqualified
and we're in the next round.

841
01:14:05,571 --> 01:14:10,325
Get your pads on for practice. We're
going to war with Tucker Friday night.

842
01:14:19,376 --> 01:14:22,421
<i>Welcome to the GISA quarterfinals.</i>

843
01:14:22,546 --> 01:14:25,966
Who would have thought we'd be seeing
the Shiloh Eagles tonight

844
01:14:26,049 --> 01:14:28,135
in a contest against the Tucker Tigers?

845
01:14:28,218 --> 01:14:30,262
With Princeton Heights disqualified,

846
01:14:30,387 --> 01:14:32,806
this is an early Christmas present
for Shiloh.

847
01:14:32,890 --> 01:14:35,851
Offense, put it in the end zone.
Defense, build me a wall.

848
01:14:35,934 --> 01:14:38,478
- Eagles on three. One, two, three.
- Eagles.

849
01:14:42,357 --> 01:14:45,777
Blue, 18. Blue, 18.

850
01:14:45,903 --> 01:14:48,280
Set. Hit. Hit.

851
01:15:11,094 --> 01:15:16,642
David. This is your field goal.
It belongs to you. Put it through.

852
01:15:23,649 --> 01:15:24,691
David.

853
01:15:27,194 --> 01:15:28,904
Hit.

854
01:15:31,949 --> 01:15:33,992
Yes.

855
01:15:36,995 --> 01:15:39,498
The Tucker Tigers
are nursing their wounds

856
01:15:39,623 --> 01:15:41,625
as they face the end of their season.

857
01:15:41,750 --> 01:15:44,711
The Eagles, however,
have a little farther to fly.

858
01:15:45,921 --> 01:15:48,215
What kind of sick are we talking about?

859
01:15:48,298 --> 01:15:51,260
I've just felt really nauseous
the last two mornings.

860
01:15:51,343 --> 01:15:55,180
- And then I feel fine again.
- You haven't eaten anything weird?

861
01:15:55,305 --> 01:15:57,432
Not unless fruit and cereal's weird.

862
01:15:58,725 --> 01:16:02,646
Brooke, my gut says make an appointment
with the doctor.

863
01:16:02,771 --> 01:16:07,067
I've been there three times this year.
It's getting embarrassing.

864
01:16:07,150 --> 01:16:10,279
I'm just telling you what I would do.
You can even use my car.

865
01:16:15,242 --> 01:16:18,954
<i>With five seconds left, the score</i>
<i>still stands in Oakhaven's favor</i>

866
01:16:19,037 --> 01:16:20,998
<i>17 to 14 over the Eagles.</i>

867
01:16:21,123 --> 01:16:23,250
<i>Grant Taylor calls the play</i>
<i>to Zach Avery,</i>

868
01:16:23,333 --> 01:16:26,628
<i>who pulls the huddle together</i>
<i>for their last shot at going to state.</i>

869
01:16:26,753 --> 01:16:30,257
<i>It's third down and goal for the Eagles</i>
<i>and the crowd is going crazy.</i>

870
01:16:30,382 --> 01:16:33,969
<i>They line up in an "i" formation.</i>
<i>This is do or die for the Eagles.</i>

871
01:16:34,052 --> 01:16:37,264
<i>Zach takes the snap and will give it</i>
<i>to Jacob... No, it's a fake.</i>

872
01:16:37,347 --> 01:16:41,310
<i>He's got Nathan Markle open in the</i>
<i>corner. The pass is up... He's got it.</i>

873
01:16:41,393 --> 01:16:44,605
<i>Touchdown Eagles. Touchdown Eagles.</i>

874
01:16:44,688 --> 01:16:50,027
<i>Zach Avery faked out the defense</i>
<i>and made a perfect pass to win 20 to 17.</i>

875
01:16:50,152 --> 01:16:55,574
<i>Can you believe this? The Shiloh Eagles</i>
<i>are headed to the state championship.</i>

876
01:16:55,699 --> 01:17:00,495
<i>A team with only 32 players</i>
<i>has made it to the big dance. Oh, my.</i>

877
01:17:00,579 --> 01:17:03,498
On the eve of the GISA
football state championship,

878
01:17:03,624 --> 01:17:08,253
the Richland Giants prepare to defend
their reign as lords of the gridiron.

879
01:17:08,378 --> 01:17:10,631
It's no surprise they've returned.

880
01:17:10,714 --> 01:17:13,884
What is surprising is
who they're playing, the Shiloh Eagles,

881
01:17:14,009 --> 01:17:17,179
who started the season 0 and 3,
have come out of nowhere,

882
01:17:17,304 --> 01:17:19,723
and through a bizarre
set of circumstances

883
01:17:19,848 --> 01:17:22,935
now face a team
almost three times their size.

884
01:17:32,152 --> 01:17:34,279
Sleep at all last night?

885
01:17:36,907 --> 01:17:39,159
Are you nervous?

886
01:17:39,243 --> 01:17:40,911
It's a weird emotion.

887
01:17:41,036 --> 01:17:44,540
Part of me thinks
we're gonna get crushed tonight,

888
01:17:44,665 --> 01:17:47,251
part of me thinks
God may do something awesome.

889
01:17:47,376 --> 01:17:50,546
Sounds like your fear's
about to clobber your faith.

890
01:17:52,798 --> 01:17:55,008
Something like that.

891
01:17:55,092 --> 01:17:57,719
When are you going out there?

892
01:17:57,803 --> 01:18:00,138
I might leave early,
if that's all right.

893
01:18:00,264 --> 01:18:02,933
Don't worry about me.
I'll just meet you at the game.

894
01:18:03,058 --> 01:18:05,185
OK.

895
01:18:06,937 --> 01:18:10,858
Either way, you're still playing
for a state championship.

896
01:18:33,255 --> 01:18:35,924
- Where's the duck?
- Duck.

897
01:18:36,008 --> 01:18:38,343
- Zebra.
- Zebra.

898
01:18:38,468 --> 01:18:40,429
Zebra. Cat.

899
01:18:40,554 --> 01:18:42,556
- Cat.
- Meow.

900
01:18:42,681 --> 01:18:44,224
Meow.

901
01:18:44,349 --> 01:18:48,187
- There's the pig.
- Brooke Taylor's here again.

902
01:18:49,229 --> 01:18:51,565
Maybe she'll be pregnant this time.

903
01:18:51,648 --> 01:18:53,609
I hope so.

904
01:18:56,028 --> 01:18:59,281
- <i>You ready, son?</i>
- <i>I can't find my cleats.</i>

905
01:18:59,406 --> 01:19:01,033
<i>They're right here by the door.</i>

906
01:19:01,158 --> 01:19:02,409
Thanks.

907
01:19:06,288 --> 01:19:09,583
Do you realize you're playing
for the state championship?

908
01:19:09,666 --> 01:19:13,629
I don't know why I'm so nervous.
I'm not even gonna play.

909
01:19:13,712 --> 01:19:16,715
- You know I'm proud of you, don't you?
- Yes, sir.

910
01:19:16,840 --> 01:19:21,261
Don't ever doubt it. Whether you play
or not, I'll be there praying for you.

911
01:19:21,386 --> 01:19:22,721
Thanks, Dad.

912
01:19:22,846 --> 01:19:25,474
Let's go pick a fight with some giants.

913
01:19:29,061 --> 01:19:31,480
Here's the results for B Taylor.

914
01:19:31,563 --> 01:19:33,524
I'll take that.

915
01:19:36,777 --> 01:19:38,737
- Negative?
- Yes.

916
01:20:45,470 --> 01:20:47,764
I will still love you, Lord.

917
01:20:50,601 --> 01:20:52,895
I will still love you.

918
01:22:16,603 --> 01:22:20,315
All right, God. You got us here.

919
01:22:20,440 --> 01:22:23,402
Whatever happens, may you get the glory.

920
01:22:36,456 --> 01:22:40,377
- Coach, what are you doing here?
- You're at the state championship.

921
01:22:40,502 --> 01:22:43,714
Any time a former player
gets this far, you know I'd be there.

922
01:22:43,839 --> 01:22:46,341
- It blows me away.
- How you feeling?

923
