He don't think he can do it.

1133
01:38:47,886 --> 01:38:51,807
I don't have any more timeouts.
Call a timeout, Bobby Lee.

1134
01:38:51,890 --> 01:38:55,018
- This kid can't kick that far.
- Call that timeout.

1135
01:38:55,143 --> 01:38:58,063
Call a timeout anyway
and let's ice him.

1136
01:39:03,193 --> 01:39:07,781
David, come here. You're telling
yourself you're gonna miss this kick.

1137
01:39:07,865 --> 01:39:09,491
Coach, it's too far.

1138
01:39:09,616 --> 01:39:13,495
Listen to me. Do you think
God could help you make this kick?

1139
01:39:13,620 --> 01:39:16,081
- Do you believe it, David?
- Yeah, if he wants to.

1140
01:39:16,164 --> 01:39:19,001
So do I. Give me your best
and leave the rest up to him.

1141
01:39:19,084 --> 01:39:21,253
Will you do that for me?

1142
01:39:29,887 --> 01:39:32,264
Make this field goal or not,
we'll praise him.

1143
01:39:32,347 --> 01:39:36,935
But don't you walk off this field
having done any less than your best.

1144
01:39:56,288 --> 01:39:58,832
- Can I help you?
- Don't touch me.

1145
01:39:58,916 --> 01:40:01,710
I'm standing for my son.

1146
01:40:03,253 --> 01:40:06,048
God, help me make this kick.

1147
01:40:11,762 --> 01:40:14,515
Take it now. Take it now.

1148
01:40:14,598 --> 01:40:16,391
Hit.

1149
01:40:23,982 --> 01:40:28,153
<i>The kick is up. It's on its way.</i>
<i>It's long enough. It's high enough.</i>

1150
01:40:28,237 --> 01:40:30,906
<i>It's good. It's good. It's good.</i>

1151
01:40:30,989 --> 01:40:34,326
- <i>The Eagles have won the championship.</i>
- Thank you, God.

1152
01:40:34,409 --> 01:40:38,288
<i>I can't believe what I've just seen.</i>
<i>I cannot believe what I've just seen.</i>

1153
01:40:38,413 --> 01:40:40,374
A miracle has occurred here.

1154
01:40:40,457 --> 01:40:45,128
<i>The Shiloh Eagles have defeated</i>
<i>the Richland Giants 24 to 23</i>

1155
01:40:45,254 --> 01:40:47,881
to take the state title
for the first time.

1156
01:40:47,965 --> 01:40:51,009
It's incredible.
It's absolutely unbelievable.

1157
01:40:52,928 --> 01:40:56,181
You are state champion.
You are state champion.

1158
01:41:25,794 --> 01:41:29,256
All right. You guys,
who's the state champions?

1159
01:41:37,014 --> 01:41:38,974
OK. OK.

1160
01:41:39,099 --> 01:41:43,312
I got something to say. David Childers.

1161
01:41:48,400 --> 01:41:51,486
Don't you ever let anyone tell you
that you're under par,

1162
01:41:51,612 --> 01:41:53,947
second-rate or inferior.

1163
01:41:55,782 --> 01:41:58,744
I just watched God
do a miracle through you.

1164
01:41:58,827 --> 01:42:01,872
I saw a field of Giants,
85 of 'em to be exact,

1165
01:42:01,997 --> 01:42:04,249
fall in defeat.

1166
01:42:04,333 --> 01:42:06,668
Now you tell me
what's impossible with God.

1167
01:42:06,752 --> 01:42:08,712
Nothing, Coach.

1168
01:42:10,506 --> 01:42:15,177
Zach, I just watched you and the offense
do what they said could not be done.

1169
01:42:15,302 --> 01:42:19,431
- Tell me what's impossible with God.
- Nothing, Coach.

1170
01:42:19,515 --> 01:42:24,645
Brock, how about it?
You built that stone wall and it stood.

1171
01:42:24,728 --> 01:42:28,524
- Tell me what's impossible with God.
- Nothing, Coach.

1172
01:42:28,607 --> 01:42:31,276
- Scott, what's impossible with God?
- Nothing.

1173
01:42:31,360 --> 01:42:35,197
Are you sure? Those Giants are big.
They outnumber us three to one.

1174
01:42:35,280 --> 01:42:37,533
Sure there's nothing impossible
with God?

1175
01:42:37,616 --> 01:42:39,451
I'm sure, Coach.

1176
01:42:39,535 --> 01:42:42,913
- Nathan, what's impossible with God?
- Nothing, Coach.

1177
01:42:43,038 --> 01:42:45,707
- Jonathan?
- Nothing.

1178
01:42:45,791 --> 01:42:48,252
- Are you positive?
- Positive, Coach.

1179
01:42:48,377 --> 01:42:51,880
So am I. So am I.

1180
01:42:52,005 --> 01:42:55,050
God can do whatever he wants to do,
however he wants to do it.

1181
01:42:55,175 --> 01:42:58,887
And he chooses to work in our lives
'cause he loves us, 'cause he's good.

1182
01:43:00,013 --> 01:43:04,726
Hope today's a milestone for what
he can do for the rest of your life,

1183
01:43:04,810 --> 01:43:07,354
if you trust him.

1184
01:43:07,479 --> 01:43:11,024
Let's spend some time thanking him.

1185
01:43:27,374 --> 01:43:30,294
Look who just walked in this house.

1186
01:43:30,419 --> 01:43:34,089
Couldn't be the state champion coach
Grant Taylor, could it?

1187
01:43:34,214 --> 01:43:36,717
'Cause he's not supposed to live here.

1188
01:43:36,800 --> 01:43:40,387
He's supposed to be out
looking for a job.

1189
01:43:40,512 --> 01:43:44,099
God did it, Brooke.

1190
01:43:44,224 --> 01:43:46,059
He did it.

1191
01:43:48,896 --> 01:43:52,649
He gave me this job,

1192
01:43:52,774 --> 01:43:55,444
provided for our needs,

1193
01:43:55,527 --> 01:43:58,989
took away my fear.

1194
01:43:59,114 --> 01:44:02,284
He throws in the state championship
just 'cause he can.

1195
01:44:08,207 --> 01:44:11,543
It's been one of the best days
of my life.

1196
01:44:11,627 --> 01:44:15,714
- The day's not over yet.
- What do you mean?

1197
01:44:17,007 --> 01:44:22,596
Grant Taylor, I just want you to know
that you've made the team.

1198
01:44:23,722 --> 01:44:25,682
What team?

1199
01:44:28,143 --> 01:44:30,979
The daddy team.

1200
01:44:33,649 --> 01:44:35,776
We're gonna have a baby?

1201
01:44:35,859 --> 01:44:38,153
We're gonna have a baby.

1202
01:44:45,994 --> 01:44:48,622
You tell me, Coach Taylor,

1203
01:44:48,705 --> 01:44:53,544
tell me what's impossible
when God's on your side?

1204
01:44:56,255 --> 01:44:59,925
Oh, God. Oh, God. I'm overwhelmed.

